@startuml state-project
!theme plain

title Power Atlas -- Project Status State Machine
caption Lifecycle states for a power calculation project

skinparam stateBorderColor #555555
skinparam stateBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam stateArrowColor #444444
skinparam noteBorderColor #888888

[*] --> draft : "Engineer creates\nnew project"

state draft : Project is newly created.
state draft : Loads can be added/edited.
state draft : Layout can be designed.
state draft : No reports generated yet.

state active : Project is in active use.
state active : Calculations are finalized.
state active : Reports can be generated.
state active : Activity is logged.

state archived : Project is stored for reference.
state archived : Read-only access.
state archived : No new loads or edits.
state archived : Reports still downloadable.

draft --> active : "Engineer activates project\n[at least 1 load exists]"
active --> archived : "Engineer archives project\n(completed or inactive)"
archived --> active : "Engineer reactivates project\n(needs further work)"

note right of draft
  **Initial state** for all new projects.
  PRN is assigned on creation.
  Status stored in projects.status column.
end note

note right of active
  Most work happens here:
  load management, calculations,
  report generation, layout design.
end note

note left of archived
  Soft archive -- data is preserved.
  Can be restored to active if
  the project needs revisiting.
end note

@enduml
